<P>
 Darren Daulton had a cancerous mole removed from his stomach last week and 
doctors declared the Philadelphia Phillies' catcher in good health. 
</P>
<P>
 The mole, which was in early cancer stages, was removed last Tuesday. Biopsy 
results became available later, Phillie spokesman Larry Shenk said. 
</P>
<P>
 "The surgery was a success. He's 100% cured, 100% healthy. There's no more 
tests, no more treatments, anything, for it," Shenk said. "That's kind of a 
common skin cancer that people have." 
</P>
<P>
 Daulton is the second Phillie player to undergo a cancer operation this year. 
First baseman John Kruk had a cancerous testicle removed March 8 and underwent 
several weeks of low-dose radiation treatment. Boxing 
</P>
