<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL NOTES: CECIL GETS MISSION VIEJO BASEBALL JOB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jeff Cecil, an assistant coach at Laguna Hills the last two seasons, has been 
named varsity baseball coach at Mission Viejo High, pending approval by the 
Saddleback Valley Unified School District Board of Trustees. 
</P>
<P>
 Cecil replaces Pat Wren, who resigned after one season in which the Diablos 
went 4-20 and 1-14 in the South Coast League.Before coming to Laguna Hills, 
Cecil was head coach at La Verne Damien High for one season. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Jagd was re-hired as the girls' volleyball coach at El Toro High. Jagd 
coached the South Coast League champion El Toro boys' volleyball team last 
season and coached the El Toro girls' team from 1985-1991. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 George Fuller, who has been an assistant basketball coach for the past 10 
years at Grand Valley State in Allendale, Mich., has been named to a similar 
position at Cal State Fullerton by Coach Brad Holland. 
</P>
<P>
 Fuller's brother, Tony, is the head coach at Pepperdine and was an assistant 
with Holland at UCLA under Coach Jim Harrick. 
</P>
<P>
 Fuller replaces Chris Brazier on the Titan staff, which also includes Bob 
Hawking and George Tuttle. 
</P>
<P>
 Fuller was a starting point guard for three conference championship seasons 
under Coach Tony Villemure, who hired him as an assistant. He graduated from 
Grand Valley State in 1978 and received a master's degree in 1983. 
</P>
<P>
 Grand Valley has been 101-42 in the last five seasons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
