<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: BREA; FEST BOASTS AN ARRAY OF ART, MUSIC, FOOD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city's cultural arts programs will be showcased at "Brea Fest, a Taste of 
the Arts." 
</P>
<P>
 Admission is free to this annual event, which is scheduled for 7 to 10:30 p.m. 
Friday at the Brea Civic and Cultural Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Music will be performed on three outdoor stages that evening. Featured will be 
country-Western music by High Noon, reggae by Trinidad and Tobago Showboat, and 
Motown tunes by the Derek Bordeaux Group. 
</P>
<P>
 Classical guitarists and a comedian also will appear. 
</P>
<P>
 Theatrical performances will be presented by the Brea Civic Light Opera, the 
Brea Youth Theatre, Prism Productions and the Vanguard Theatre Ensemble. 
</P>
<P>
 Also appearing will be dancers from the Brea Dance Center and from Imperial 
Dance Studios. Recording artist Dave Kinnoin will perform children's music. 
</P>
<P>
 Among the art displays scheduled for Brea Fest is an exhibit titled 
"Inspirations: Art by the Physically and Mentally Challenged." 
</P>
<P>
 Food and beverages for sale at the event have been donated by Orange County 
restaurants and food distributors. 
</P>
<P>
 All proceeds will support Brea's cultural arts programs. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 990-7735.ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
</TEXT>
