<HEADLINE>
<P>
VIOLENCE PREVENTION PROGRAM TO BE OFFERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Residents are welcome to attend a weekly support group and workshop at 
Saddleback College on the prevention of domestic violence. 
</P>
<P>
 The meetings run from 5 to 7 p.m. Wednesdays at the Adult Opportunity and 
Women's Center, in the college's Student Services Center, 28000 Marguerite 
Parkway. 
</P>
<P>
 The meetings are intended for anyone who is in an abusive relationship, or 
those concerned about relatives and friends who may be in abusive 
relationships. 
</P>
<P>
 Staff members of Human Options, a battered women's shelter in Laguna Beach, 
facilitate the meetings. For information, call (714) 582-4611. 
</P>
</TEXT>
