<HEADLINE>
<P>
MEASURE Z HARD-WON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 To answer Timothy Freeman's complaint about the well-organized, unopposed Save 
Our Port Hueneme Police Department campaign: Pay attention to the facts, and 
you will know our City Council is not stealthily voting in anything. How 
ludicrous. 
</P>
<P>
 Eight months of hard work gave us close to 65% of the vote on Measure Z. Why 
was the campaign unopposed? Why did we have money to spend? The majority of the 
people want our city to remain crime-free and safe. 
</P>
<P>
 Four months before the election, the City Council discussed the utility tax 
and it was reported in the paper. The council went with the majority of the 
voters, which is right. I am flattered Mr. Freeman feels our committee was so 
powerful that we could appeal to the City Council after the election and have 
them bow to us and pass a utility tax. That is not how the city works. Our city 
is saved, and there are no bums here. 
</P>
<P>
 VALORIE MORRISON 
</P>
<P>
 Port Hueneme 
</P>
<P>
 Valorie Morrison is chairwoman of the Save Our Port Hueneme Police Department 
steering committee . 
</P>
