<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALLOW VOTE ON LANDFILL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The initiative process can be the only method by which voters move elected 
officials to action. 
</P>
<P>
 At this particular moment, the issue concerning the Weldon Canyon landfill is 
not that of the landfill itself.It is the issue of whether or not the voters of 
the county are to be allowed to vote on an issue vital to their welfare. 
</P>
<P>
 For years we have heard the fantasy proposals ranging from recycling 
everything to shipping the rubbish to someone else's back yard. To date we have 
had no reliable dates of attainability of total recycling nor any solid 
consumer cost for rail haul. 
</P>
<P>
 A solution to our rubbish problems must be effected, and since Weldon Canyon 
has been identified in the environmental document as the preferred location, at 
least let us vote. 
</P>
<P>
 ELOISE BROWN 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark 
</P>
</TEXT>
