<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAVERICK'S GOOD DEAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Recently, Maverick's restaurant in Simi Valley was the subject in "Restaurant 
Review" in Ventura County Life. The review confirmed the fact that this is only 
one man's opinion, so we feel justified to give ours. 
</P>
<P>
 To begin with, the amount of people who frequent Maverick's is enough to give 
it a five-star rating. Customers don't go back to the same place week after 
week if the food and service is lacking. 
</P>
<P>
 We could go on and on but instead of taking your reviewer's opinion or ours, 
try it yourselves. You won't come away hungry, and you will go back not only 
for the food but for the service, which will make you feel at home every time. 
</P>
<P>
 One added note: Maverick's was in the middle of the hardest hit area in Simi 
in our recent earthquake and took a real beating. However, Maverick's staff 
didn't waste time and moved outside to feed our forgotten corner of the world. 
</P>
<P>
 These are good people who wouldn't know how to serve anything but good food 
and provide excellent service. 
</P>
<P>
 RICHARD and JO ANN FISKE 
</P>
<P>
 Simi Valley 
</P>
</TEXT>
