<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: KOREATOWN; ARMORED 
TRUCK GUARDS KILL ROBBER, POLICE SAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An armed man was fatally wounded Monday while allegedly trying to rob three 
armored truck guards near a Bank of America branch in Koreatown, police said.  
</P>
<P>
 The man wounded in the 8:26 a.m. shooting at Olympic Boulevard and Western 
Avenue died at Cedars-Sinai Medical Center, said Los Angeles Police Lt. Ken 
Lady. 
</P>
<P>
 Three Loomis armored truck guards had just made a delivery to the bank and 
were returning to their truck when the gunman walked toward a nearby bus bench 
and stopped, Lady said. 
</P>
<P>
 As the guards got close to the man, whose identity was not released pending 
notification of next of kin, he pulled a revolver from his waistband and 
pointed it at them, Lady said. Two of the guards then opened fire, wounding the 
gunman.  
</P>
<P>
 Police questioned a man seen running from the scene, but he was released. They 
said the slain robber apparently acted alone. 
</P>
