ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; MAN FATALLY STABBED AFTER DOMESTIC FIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK I. PINSKY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 25-year-old man was stabbed to death just before midnight Sunday after a 
domestic fight, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, who lived in Anaheim, has not been identified by police. 
</P>
<P>
 Marco Diaz, 30, of Garden Grove was arrested on suspicion of murder, Sgt. 
Steve Rodig said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police were called to a home in the 2800 block of West Ball Road after a 
report of an assault on a woman by her live-in boyfriend, who fled the scene. 
</P>
<P>
 While investigating, authorities heard a dispute nearby between Diaz and the 
woman's boyfriend, Rodig said. Rodig said Diaz is a friend of the woman. 
</P>
<P>
 Diaz stabbed the man and tried to flee but was arrested and was being held at 
the Anaheim City Jail, police said. No bail has been set, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The unidentified man was treated at the scene by paramedics and taken to UCI 
Medical Center in Orange, where he died.MARK I. PINSKY 
