<P>
PEOPLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Bloomberg Business News 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Price Waterhouse said it nominated James J. Schiro as chairman and senior 
partner of the accounting firm. 
</P>
<P>
 Schiro, 48, was nominated to succeed Shaun F. O'Malley next July 1.O'Malley 
will have reached the accounting firm's mandatory retirement age of 60. 
</P>
<P>
 The nomination is subject to approval of the firm's approximate 970 partners, 
a process that is under way. A spokeswoman said the firm expects to complete 
the vote in mid-September. 
</P>
<P>
 Schiro is vice chairman for the firm's metropolitan New York region. He has 
been a partner of the firm since 1979. Price Waterhouse spokeswoman Jan Butler 
said Schiro was traveling and unavailable for comment. 
</P>
<P>
 Schiro built a track record for bringing in clients while working in the New 
York area, the "most competitive single marketplace," said Rick Telberg, editor 
of Accounting Today, an industry publication. 
</P>
<P>
 In succeeding O'Malley, Telberg added, Schiro will have tough shoes to fill. 
Price Waterhouse is coming off its best year ever, with fees up 10% and 
consulting revenue up 20%, he said. 
</P>
