DEALS: COMPANY TOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES BATES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Television: Call it Disney goes Deutschland. The entertainment giant is 
joining with European television broadcaster Compagnie Luxembourgeoise de 
Telediffusion Multi Media to launch a new family channel in Germany starting in 
January.The satellite-cable channel will be called Super RTL. CLT, which has 
interests in 10 television stations and 13 radio stations in nine countries, is 
a major shareholder in Europe's RTL Television and RTL2 channel. Programs 
offered over the channel are expected to include animated series, live- action 
shows, feature films and entertainment specials. The channel is expected to 
reach up to 35% of German television homes when it is launched. As part of the 
deal, Disney agreed to be a long-term supplier of programs to CLT Multi Media 
and to join the company in developing services in other markets. Disney 
Chairman Michael D. Eisner said the venture will allow Disney to evaluate the 
potential for similar European services. CLT's shareholders include Belgium 
Group, France's Group Havas and the Paribas Group. JAMES BATES 
</P>
