Compiled by John O'Dell, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Orange County has lost more than a dozen new car dealerships in recent years, 
but hope springs eternal in the souls of those who sell automobiles. 
</P>
<P>
 Costa Mesa-based Nabers Automotive Group, which runs Nabers Cadillac and 
Buick, has opened Nabers Isuzu four blocks farther north on Harbor Boulevard, 
just off the San Diego Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
 The new lot opened about a month ago after Nabers acquired the Isuzu franchise 
that Theodore Robins Ford was abandoning in order to make room for its expanded 
Ford truck center. 
</P>
