<P>
 Dense-Pac Microsystems Inc.: The firm announced Monday it has received a 
$750,000 order from E-Systems, based in Greenville, Tex., for computer memory 
chips that function in rough environments. 
</P>
<P>
 E-Systems will use the chips in its avionics sales, company officials said. 
Deliveries are scheduled over the next 90 days. The chips are ceramic and will 
be used in things like planes, satellites and missiles, where there is too much 
bouncing around to install a hard drive to handle memory needs. 
</P>
