<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cerplex Group Inc.: The company announced Monday it has bought a technical 
training and repair services company in Redmond, Wash., from the company's 
founders. 
</P>
<P>
 Cerplex spokesman Bruce Nye declined to say how much the Anaheim-based company 
paid for Apex Computer Co. Inc., which had revenues of about $12 million last 
fiscal year. Cerplex does not plan to shift Apex's 53 employees from their 
Washington work site, Nye said. 
</P>
<P>
 Like Apex, Cerplex provides electronic repair and parts servicing, but had not 
focused on training until this acquisition. The move will also allow Cerplex to 
offer its services to companies whose computers use the UNIX operating system 
and to begin building a presence in the Pacific Northwest, Nye said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
