<HEADLINE>
<P>
DOWNTIME: BODY WATCH; DANCES WITH COYOTES AND DEER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I run trails in the canyons in the Santa Monica mountains.I've run into bees, 
poison oak and rattlesnakes. I have seen hawks, rabbits, coyotes, deer and 
bobcats. I know the canyons turn green, then gold, then brown, year after year, 
and I have seen them turn black after fire. I have learned to hear my 
footsteps, to listen to my breathing. There is a rhythm in the trail and in me. 
We're a dance. 
</P>
<P>
 -- CATHY CABALLERO, Malibu 
</P>
</TEXT>
