<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: SANTIAGO; SOUTHERN CONE TALKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 President Carlos Saul Menem of Argentina will come to Santiago on Thursday for 
a two-day session with Chilean President Eduardo Frei.The meeting is a 
manifestation of increasingly close ties between the neighboring South American 
countries, which were on the verge of war in 1978. 
</P>
<P>
 Chile and Argentina are planning improved highways to cross their Andean 
frontier and a pipeline to bring Argentine gas to Santiago. 
</P>
<P>
 A major subject of discussion is expected to be negotiations for a trade 
agreement between Chile and Mercosur, the duty-free zone being formed by 
Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA082394-0194 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 072423 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
August 23, 1994, Tuesday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
World Report; Page 1; Column 1; World Report 
</P>
</SECTION>
