<P>
11 KILLED IN HEAD-ON CRASH OF 2 VEHICLES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A sports utility vehicle crossed the center line, slammed head-on into a sedan 
packed with passengers and burst into flames, killing all 11 people in both 
vehicles, police said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 The dead included five children, ages 2 to 6, who were among the nine people 
in the car. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident occurred Sunday evening when the southbound Chevy Blazer collided 
with the northbound Chevrolet Caprice, Lt. Bob Dale of the state patrol said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Blazer's fuel line apparently ruptured, and all the victims were severely 
burned in the ensuing fire, Dale said. 
</P>
<P>
 No one reported witnessing the accident on Alternate U.S. 97 about two miles 
north of this central Washington city, and it was not known how fast the 
vehicles were traveling, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The weather was clear and dry at the time of the crash. 
