<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL STRIKE: DEVELOPMENTS FROM DAY 11 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Games lost: 10. 
</P>
<P>
 * Total games lost: 141. 
</P>
<P>
 * Games remaining: 528. 
</P>
<P>
 * Total income lost by players: $48.6 million. 
</P>
<P>
 * Estimated revenue lost by owners: $93.5 million. 
</P>
<P>
 * Key development: Union head Donald Fehr and management negotiator Richard 
Ravitch met with federal mediators. 
</P>
<P>
 * In quotes: "The owners want to drastically lower player salaries. Dick's the 
assigned hatchet man to go and get it done. Dick is not an independent figure 
here." 
</P>
<P>
 -- Donald Fehr 
</P>
</TEXT>
