<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: PERCEPTRONICS INC. HAS 1ST-QUARTER PROFIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Perceptronics Inc., a Woodland Hills developer of computer simulation 
programs, said its profit for the fiscal first quarter that ended June 30 was 
$39,407, compared to a loss of $480,849 in the same quarter the previous year. 
Revenue for the first quarter was $1.83 million, down 4% from $1.90 million the 
year before. 
</P>
<P>
 The company attributed the results to reductions in staff and its recent move 
into cheaper facilities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
