128 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: AUTHENTIC FITNESS' EARNINGS RISE 72% IN 4TH QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Authentic Fitness Corp., a Van Nuys-based apparel concern, reported a 72% jump 
in its fiscal fourth-quarter earnings. The gain was a result, the company said, 
of continued growth of its Speedo swimwear and active-wear lines, its Cole, 
Anne Cole and Catalina brands and a strong performance by its retail stores. 
</P>
<P>
 However, Authentic Fitness' profit fell 18% for the fiscal year ended July 2. 
</P>
<P>
 In the fourth quarter, the company earned $4.35 million, up from $2.54 million 
in net income a year earlier. Its quarterly revenue grew 38%, to $59.8 million 
from $43.4 million. 
</P>
<P>
 For fiscal 1994, Authentic Fitness had earnings of $7.99 million, down from a 
$9.78-million profit the previous year. Its annual revenue rose 34%, to $178.6 
million from $132.9 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Corporate Earnings 
</P>
